The paper deals with the problem of super resolution of binary document images using deep neural networks, which is a topic that falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The proposed models are all based on deep learning techniques (cs.DL) and involve the use of convolutional layers (cs.LG) for feature extraction and sub-pixel convolution layers for upscaling the features. Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the models in terms of OCR accuracy (cs.CL).
